cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper deals with optimizing the throughput of a network by considering power allocation and caching strategy jointly. It specifically focuses on fiber-wireless (FiWi) access networks, which are a type of wireless network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory (IT) and cryptography (CR) concepts, which makes cs.IT and cs.CR likely categories as well. The paper proposes a dynamic programming algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing system performance, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
